She still wears her father's bracelet and carries a memorial card in her hat. 

'There's not a second that goes by I don't think of my father. There's so much that reminds me of him,” she said. 

'Being a firefighter himself, he knows what comes with the job. But he would know it I'd be able to handle it, he knows how strong I am,' she said.

 

